== Republics and Camps of the IFM-SEI ==

There were four children's republics held by the international before [[World War II]] they were:
* 1933 First Republic : Oostduinkerke, {{Flag|Belgium}} .
* 1935 Second Republic : Verneuil-l'Étang, {{Flag|France}} . 900 children from Austria, Belgium, Czechoslovakia, France, UK and Switzerland.
* 1937 Third Republic : Brighton, {{Flag|United Kingdom}} . Theme: [[Solidarity]], 2,000 participants from Belgium, Czechoslovakia, France, Britain, Spain and Tunisia.
* 1939 Fourth Republic : Wandre, {{Flag|Belgium}} . Theme: [[Political freedom|Freedom]] and [[Peace]], 1,600 participants, from Belgium, France, UK, Switzerland, Tunisia and refugee children from Spain.

